HB 442 Original 2026 Regular Session Marcelle
Abstract: Provides for the election sections for judgeship of the family court for East Baton
Rouge Parish.
Statistical summaries of proposed law including maps illustrating proposed district
boundaries accompany this digest. (Attached to the bill version on the internet.)
Present law provides that the family court for the parish of East Baton Rouge will consist
of three election sections.
Proposed law retains present law.
Present law provides for the boundaries of the election sections.
Proposed law provides for the change of the boundaries of the election sections.
Present law provides that the family court of East Baton Rouge Parish is composed of four
judges. Provides that one judge is elected from election section one; one judge is elected
from election section two; and two judges are elected from election section three.
Proposed law provides that one judge, Division B, shall be elected from election section one;
one judge, Division C, shall be elected from election section two; and two judges, Divisions
A and D, shall be elected from election section three.
Proposed law specifies that precincts referenced in district descriptions are those precincts
contained in the file named "2026 Precinct Shapefiles (01-27-2026)" available on the
legislature's website. The 2026 Precinct Shapefiles are based upon Voting Districts (VTDs)
contained in the 2020 Census Redistricting TIGER/Line Shapefiles for the State of La. as
those files have been modified and validated through data verification program of the La.
House of Representatives and the La. Senate to represent precinct changes submitted through
Jan. 27, 2026, to the Legislature of La. by parish governing authorities.
Proposed law specifies that if any such precinct has been subdivided by action of the parish
governing authority on a nongeographic basis or subdivided by action of the parish
